sinopse:
The setup is honestly great...
A hurricane flooding a small town;
Sharks swimming through the streets;
People trapped in cars and houses.That should be terrifying, right?But the movie plays it way too safe. It doesn't go full horror (not scary enough). It doesn't go full chaos (not wild enough). It keeps cutting away from moments that should hit hard.Instead of unforgettable scenes, you just get a lot of "that could've been amazing" moments. What a shame!!
